Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Redclaw crayfish (_Cherax quadricarinatus_) / 71.43 percent / 66.16 percent / 92.63 percent / 66.16 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and / or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the crayfish plague infection, which is notifiable to the OIE, was detected on 5 crayfish farms in the process of passive surveillance (reported cases) and identified as _Aphanomyces astaci_ infection. Movement restriction was implemented on the infected farms. The clinical and epidemiological investigations of surrounding crayfish farms were conducted. No other case or evidence of crayfish plague infection was detected.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine; movement control inside the country; disinfection of infected premises / establishment (s); surveillance outside containment and / or buffer zone; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Pingtung University of Science and Technology (local laboratory) / Redclaw crayfish (_Cherax quadricarinatus_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 6 Dec 2013 / Positive
National Pingtung University of Science and Technology (local laboratory) / Redclaw crayfish (_Cherax quadricarinatus_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 9 Dec 2013 / Positive
National Pingtung University of Science and Technology (local laboratory) / Redclaw crayfish (_Cherax quadricarinatus_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 9 Jan 2014 / Positive
Animal Health Research Institute (AHRI) (national laboratory) / Redclaw crayfish (_Cherax quadricarinatus_) / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 17 Feb 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

